%N A395443 Squares visited by seven knights, all starting on square 1, when moving on a square-spiral numbered board and always moving to the lowest available unvisited square.
%C A395443 All seven knights, numbered 1..7, start at square one, and each moves in turn to the lowest available unvisited square, starting with the lowest numbered knight.
%C A395443 The sequence is finite - knight 2 is trapped on square 1219 after visiting 195 squares, knight 7 is trapped on square 3213 after visiting 529 squares, knight 6 is trapped on square 4723 after visiting 719 squares, knight 3 is trapped on square 18410 after visiting 3190 squares, knight 4 is trapped on square 10529 after visiting 3197 squares, knight 1 is trapped on square 17995 after visiting 4269 squares, and knight 5 is trapped on square 20471 after visiting 8373 squares, giving a total of 20466 visited squares.
%H A395443 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A395443/b395443.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20466</a>
%H A395443 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A395443/a395443.png">Image of the knights' paths</a>. The knights' paths are colored red, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet and light gray, the final squares for knights 1..4, 6, 7 are colored yellow, and the final square for knight 5 is colored red.
%Y A395443 Cf. A338290, A395439-A395442, A395444, A316667.
